INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (326, 2, '2009-11-22 21:48:55', '2009-11-23 04:48:55', '<img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-268" title="Potato Latkes" src="http://www.cookingandmore.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/KRUGEL2-150x150.jpg" alt="Potato Latkes" width="150" height="150" />\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Dear Friends,</p>\r\n\r\nThanksgiving, Hanukkah, Christmas, New Years, we are very busy this time of year!  Regardless of which holiday you are celebrating, there is still alot of cooking and eating going on and I am here to help!\r\n\r\nStarting with Thanksgiving, check out my alternative <strong>Turkey My Mother\'s Way</strong> preparation that does not include frying or cream gravy.  Cook the bird over a bed of vegetables and when the turkey is done you also have an additional vegetable side dish and rich, aromatic, clear gravy to serve over your meat and potatoes.  Don\'t forget the <strong>Sweet Potato Cazuela</strong> and the incredible <strong>Mixed Fruit Relish </strong>that will last in your refrigerator all through the December holidays, if, you make a double batch!\r\n\r\nA reader brought to my attention that my <strong>Potato Latke</strong> recipe was no where to be found! What was I thinking??? But you can also check out the <strong>Ricotta Cheese Pancakes </strong>or<strong> Sweet Moroccan Couscous </strong>that are also traditional for Hanukkah in different parts of the world.\r\n\r\nAnd last, but not least, the Appetizer section should get you through the cocktail hour of any gathering of family and friends whether it be Christmas or New Years Eve.\r\n\r\nEnjoy time with your loved ones and count your blessings even if you feel there is a little less to count this year.\r\n\r\nMy <strong>Entre\'e to Judaism</strong> book tour is going very well.  If you are near where I am giving my talks, come in and make sure you introduce yourselves.  I always like to meet the people whose lives I share in a small way.\r\n\r\nDuring the next few w