INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (333, 2, '2010-01-12 14:04:06', '2010-01-12 21:04:06', '<img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-268" title="Potato Latkes" src="http://www.cookingandmore.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/KRUGEL2-150x150.jpg" alt="Potato Latkes" width="150" height="150" />\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Dear Friends,</p>\r\n\r\nHappy New Year! I hope your year is filled with joy and successful creative pursuits; especially in the kitchen!\r\n\r\nThe year has started off great but we have seen more below freezing days and snow than I can ever remember this early in the year. All the more reason to focus on wonderful hot soups and stews.  The first request from my daughter when she came home from college for winter break was her favorite Mulligatawny soup.  Warming, filling soup that can be served over rice to make a complete meal.  Perfect for cold days and tight budgets!\r\n\r\nExciting news about my book <em><strong>Entree to Judaism</strong></em>; it was listed as #7 on the Washington Posts <strong>2009 Gift Guide for Cookbooks</strong>!  Thank yous go to all of you who have made this book so successful that we are focusing now on a second printing in just 2 months.\r\n\r\nThe best part about writing the book is the opportunity it is giving me to visit so many wonderful parts of the country and meeting the nicest people one could ever hope to meet.  From Nashville to Toledo, Memphis to Indianapolis, I have been blessed with great audiences and new found friends.  And the excitement continues!  Please see the list below and come and meet me if you are in the area. I am still available for speaking engagements and classes in your hometown for 2010-2011 so contact me if you would like to discuss some options for your organization.\r\n\r\nIf I\'m not coming to you then listen to my appearance on local NPR station KERA to hear me talk about the history and stories in <strong>Entre\'e to Judaism. </strong>\r\n\r\n<a class="current" href="http://podcastdownload.npr.org/anon.npr-podcasts/podcast/77/510036/121221265/KERA_121221265.mp3?_kip_ipx=1078152060-1260833421" target="_self">http://podcastdownload.npr.org/anon.npr-podcasts/podcast/77/510036/121221265/KERA_121221265.mp3?_kip_ipx=1078152060-1260833421</a>\r\n\r\nDuring the next few weeks I will be speaking:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>January 29-31</strong>: Congregation Gates of Prayer-Metairie, LA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul></ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>February 2</strong>: Learning Fest- Dallas JCC, Dallas, TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 17</strong>: Central Market Cooking School, Ft. Worth,TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 18</strong>: Central Market Cooking School, Houston,TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 20: </strong>Central Market Cooking School, Plano, TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 21</strong>: Central Market Cooking School, Southlake, TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 22: </strong>Central Market Cooking School,Dallas, TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 24:</strong>Central Market Cooking School, San Antonio, TX</li>\r\n	<li><strong>February 25</strong>: Central Market Cooking School, Austin, TX</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEat in Good Health!\r\n\r\nTina', 'Welcome to Tina\'s Kitchen', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '209-revision-11', '', '', '2010-01-12 14:04:06', '2010-01-12 21:04:06', '', 209, 'http://www.cookingandmore.com/4/209-revision-11', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (334, 2, '2010-01-12 15:02:55', '2010-01-12 22:02:55', 'NIRVANA CHICKEN WINGS<img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-337" title="NirvanaChicken" src="http://www.cookingandmore.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/NirvanaChicken2-150x150.jpg" alt="NirvanaChicken" width="150" height="168" />\r\nI call these wings “nirvana’ because they could transport you to paradise.  Easy to make, messy to eat and loads of fun.  A modern interpretation of Indian cuisine that’s just as easy to prepare with chicken parts for a hearty main dish.\r\n\r\n4 Tablespoons margarine (you can use butter if you are not kosher)\r\n2 Tablespoons curry powder\r\n1/4 cup dry white wine\r\n2-3 pounds chicken wing drummettes or chicken cut into 1/8ths\r\n1 cup mango chutney\r\n1/4 cup shredded coconut\r\n1 Tablespoon finely chopped scallion\r\n2 Tablespoons finely chopped peanuts\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n1.    Melt the margarine in a saucepan and stir in the curry powder.  Cook for 2-3 minutes and add the wine.  Remove from heat.\r\n\r\n2.     Remove any excess fat from the chicken parts.  Wash and pat dry.  If using whole wings, discard the tip and cut the two bone section and drummettes apart.\r\n\r\n3.    Place the chicken parts in a roasting pan and baste with the curry sauce.  Bake for 20 minutes in a 350F Oven.\r\n\r\n4.    Chop up any large pieces of mango in the chutney and then spread the chutney over the chicken parts.  Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.\r\n\r\n5.    Place the chicken on a serving platter and reduce the sauce by 1/3.\r\n\r\n6.    Pour the sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with the coconut, scallions and peanuts.  Serve.\r\n\r\nNOTE:  May be made in advance and reheated in the microwave or oven.  Garnish with the coconut, scallion, and peanuts only after reheating and before serving.', 'Nirvana Chicken Wings', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nirvana-chicken-wings', '', '', '2010-02-22 22:06:12', '2010-02-23 05:06:12', '', 0, 'http://www.cookingandmore.com/?p=334', 0, 'post', '', 0); 
