INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (398, 2, '2010-03-21 20:12:57', '2010-03-22 03:12:57', '<p style="text-align: left;">Dear Friends,<img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-395" title="PassoverLinzerTart" src="http://www.cookingandmore.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/PassoverLinzerTart-150x150.jpg" alt="PassoverLinzerTart" width="150" height="150" /></p>\r\n\r\nI just had to check my bags on a flight home from California.  Why you may ask?  Because I was bringing home 2 jars of kosher for Passover raspberry preserves for my famous Linzer torte which wouldn\'t be famous this year unless I found the raspberry!  I also found a bottle of almond and vanilla extract for Passover.  If you think that is bad, you should have seen me years ago when I borrowed a suitcase from my girlfriend and went to her kosher butcher in Maryland.  the suitcase contained two soup chickens and a turkey!\r\n\r\nI don\'t have to go through such machinations anymore but both quests are illustrative of the importance of Passover, specifically the Seder, in my kitchen.\r\n\r\nI want to help you create wonderful Passover memories in your homes so check out the recipes on this site, click on the latest issue of Reform Judaism on the left to see some interesting recipes from South Africa, and go to your nearest Barnes and Noble, Neiman Marcus or order online to get <em><strong>Entree to Judaism</strong></em> (there\'s an entire chapter on Charoset as well as Passover!).\r\n\r\nWhatever you do, enjoy creating memories for your family as we remember our redemption from slavery.\r\n\r\nLet all who are hungry come and eat! and...\r\n\r\nEat in Good Health!\r\n\r\nTina\r\n\r\nHere\'s a little lesson on how to create the Linzer Torte. Enjoy!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8sxLAUrHF5Y">How to Shape a Passover Linzer Torte</a>\r\n\r\nI have to focus on Passover, but here is where I will be speaking or having book signings in the next month so come and join me\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>March 18: </strong> Dallas, TX, Tycher Library, Aaron JCC</li>\r\n	<li><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>March 25: Dallas, TX, </strong>Neiman Marcus, North Park Book Signing</li>\r\n	<li><strong>April 15: Washington, D.C., </strong>Neiman Marcus, Massa book signing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf I\'m not coming to you then <a href="http://podcastdownload.npr.org/anon.npr-podcasts/podcast/77/510036/121221265/KERA_121221265.mp3?_kip_ipx=1078152060-1260833421" target="_blank">listen to my appearance on local NPR station KERA</a> to hear me talk about the history and stories in <strong>Entre\'e to Judaism.</strong>', 'Welcome to Tina\'s Kitchen', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '209-revision-24', '', '', '2010-03-21 20:12:57', '2010-03-22 03:12:57', '', 209, 'http://www.cookingandmore.com/4/209-revision-24', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
